Grafana doesn't "have" Loki built in — you add it as a data source, exactly the same way you'd add Prometheus as a data source. 
In Grafana's UI: Connections → Data sources → Add data source → select "Loki" (or "Prometheus").

Prometheus (with Grafana on top) lets you visualize graphs for every pod, individually or aggregated, since every metric comes 
with labels identifying exactly which pod, namespace, container it belongs to.
